HEADWORD: Subhepatic
<hw>Sub`he*pat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated under, or on the ventral side of, the liver; -- applied to
the interlobular branches of the portal vein.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

